<body>

<header class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow hero-eyebrow">Pioneer of Computing</p>
      <h1>Ada<br><em>Lovelace</em></h1>
      <p class="tagline">She looked at a machine built to calculate and saw one that could compose — and in the margins of a translated memoir, she wrote the first algorithm meant for a computer that did not yet exist.</p>
      <p class="dates">10 DECEMBER 1815 — 27 NOVEMBER 1852 · LONDON</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="portrait-frame">
        <img id="portrait"
             src="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Ada_Lovelace_portrait.jpg?width=800"
             alt="Portrait of Ada Lovelace, 1838, by Alfred Edward Chalon"
             onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Ada%20Lovelace%20Chalon%20portrait.jpg?width=800';this.onerror=function(){this.onerror=null;this.src='https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Ada_Lovelace_portrait.jpg/800px-Ada_Lovelace_portrait.jpg';};">
      </div>
      <p class="portrait-caption">Portrait by Alfred Edward Chalon, 1838 — Wikimedia Commons, public domain</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="punch-strip" aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="bit off"></span><span class="bit on"></span><span class="bit off"></span><span class="bit off"></span><span class="bit off"></span><span class="bit off"></span><span class="bit off"></span><span class="bit on"></span>
